In accordance with orders from their respective state PSCs, Alabama Power and Georgia Power defer nuclear refueling outage
operations and maintenance expenses to a regulatory asset when the charges are incurred. Alabama Power amortizes the costs over
a subsequent 18-month period with Plant Farley's fall outage cost amortization beginning in January of the following year and
spring outage cost amortization beginning in July of the same year. Georgia Power amortizes its costs over each unit's operating
cycle, or 18 months for Plant Vogtle Units 1 and 2 and 24 months for Plant Hatch Units 1 and 2. Georgia Power's amortization
period begins the month the refueling outage starts.
