Mississippi Power had a net state valuation allowance of $32 million for the Mississippi NOL, Southern Power had net state
valuation allowances of $11 million for the Oklahoma NOL and $10 million for the Florida NOL, and Southern Company had a net
valuation allowance of $25 million for the New York and New York City NOLs.
The ultimate outcome of these matters cannot be determined at this time.
